Ani mne nešla gramatika, ale stačilo si to vyhľadať...


PASSIVE, čiže trpný rod sa v anglickom jazyku používa oveľa častejšie ako v
slovenčine. Do určitej miery to súvisí s nedostatkom koncoviek u anglických
podstatných a prídavných mien a s ustáleným slovosledom anglickej vety.
Pretože platí, že podmet môže byť vo vete iba pred slovesom, bolo potrebné
vytvorenie štruktúry, ktorou je práve trpný rod. Pomocou neho sa zmení na
podmet ľubovoľné podstatné meno, ktoré je vo vete s činným rodom predmetom.




ŠTRUKTÚRA TRPNÉHO RODU



PODMET + SLOVESO TO BE + MINULÉ PRÍČASTIE

V PRÍSLUŠNOM ČASE TRPNÉHO VÝZNAMOVÉHO

SLOVESA



The house was built in 1930.

I was invited to the party.

This room is cleaned every day.

Cheese is made from milk.

The car has been stolen.



This house was built in 1930. 'Was built' je trpný rod.



POROVNAJME!

ČINNÝ ROD (ACTIVE VOICE): Somebody built this house in 1930.

predmet


TRPNÝ ROD (PASSIVE VOICE): This house was built in 1930.

podmet

Činný rod používame, keď chceme povedať, čo podmet robí:

&#9679; My grandfather was a builder. He built this house in 1930.

&#9679; It´s a big company. It employs two hundred people.



Trpný rod používame, keď chceme povedať, čo sa podmetu deje:

&#9679; This house is quite old. It was built in 1930.

&#9679; Two hundred people are employed by the company.



Keď používame pasív, KTO alebo ČO (niekto urobil) je v tomto prípade neznáme,
alebo nepodstatné.

&#9679; A lot of money was stolen in the robbery. (niekto ich ukradol, ale my
nevieme KTO)

&#9679; Is this room cleaned every day? (čistí ju niekto? – nie je podstatné
KTO)



Ak ale chceme vyjadriť KTO urobil alebo ČO spôsobilo akciu, použijeme 'by'...,
napr.:

&#9679; This house was built by my grandfather.

&#9679; Two hundred people are employed by the company.





Ako sme už vyššie spomenuli, pasív sa tvorí slovesom TO BE v príslušnom čase
(is/was/have been/had been, etc) + past participle (done/cleaned/seen etc).



PRESENT SIMPLE

active: clean(s) / see(s) etc. Somebody cleans this room every day.

passive: am/is/are cleaned/seen etc. This room is cleaned every day.



&#9679; Many accidents are caused by careless driving.

&#9679; I´m not often invited to parties.

&#9679; How is this word pronounced?









PAST SIMPLE

active: clened/saw etc. Somebody cleaned this room yesterday.


passive: was/were cleaned/seen etc. This room was claned yesterday.



&#9679; We were woken up by a loud noise during the night.

&#9679; Did you go to the party? No, I wasn´t invited.

&#9679; How much money was stolen?



INFINITIVE

active: (to) do/clean/see etc. Somebody will clean the room later.

passive: (to) be done/cleaned/seen etc. The room will be cleaned later.



